          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TRD",
                "BF3"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "  Fission  fragments  were   detected   with",
                " a  multiparallel fission chamber,  the photoneutrons",
                " from (gamma,n) and (gamma,f) reactions were detected",
                " by 4pi long counter of  a Halpern type with  six BF3",
                " detectors immersed  in paraffin  where neutrons  are",
                " slowed down."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "NAICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " for gamma-flux measurement"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The photofission cross sections are related to",
                " the experimental counting rates by a system of",
                " linear equations: sum(R*sig) = (n/F)*A, which",
                " is the connection between the cross section 'sig'",
                " and gamma-ray flux 'R' at some (not main) line in",
                " photon spectrum with number of fissions 'n', main",
                " flux of photons 'F', and number of target atoms 'A'.",
                " This set of linier equations can Be solved only with",
                " some approximations. Once the solution of the",
                " quadratic system obtained from the principal lines",
                " of the elements is calculated, a linear",
                " interpolation is made between the first set of",
                " solutions, and this procedure may be repeated until",
                " the variations introduced are very small.",
                "The total cross section for neutron emission is",
                " given by: sig(gamma,n-tot) = sig(gamma,n)+",
                " 2*sig(gamma,2n) + 3*sig(gamma,3n)+...+nu*sig(gamma,F)",
                " + (1+nu)sig(gamma,nf) + (2+nu)sig(gamma,2nf)+...,",
                " where 'nu' is the number of neutrons emitted per",
                " per fission. Using long counter measured only",
                " sig(gamma,n-tot) = sig(gamma,n)+nu*sig(gamma,f)",
                " (work below the thresholds of other reactions).",
                "Substitute the latter equation to the former gives",
                " the system of linear equations, the solving of",
                " which gives the total cross section."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-S",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The errors are statistical. However since",
                "the photofission cross sections in U-235 and U-238",
                "which are presented in natural uranium are of the",
                "same order of magnitude the error committed on this",
                "assumption is of the order of the quantity of U-235",
                "in the natural uranium - about 0.7%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The (gamma,f) and (gamma,n) cross sections in U-238",
                "Th-232 and the ratio width-n/width-F were measured",
                "and with monochromatic gamma-rays, of energies from",
                "5.43 to 9.00 MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
